    <name>Key Idea: Learners’ goals should drive instruction. </name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/octae-icon-keyideasforward.png" alt="" width="140" height="136" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-top"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The primary incentive for learner
persistence is the learner’s ability to set a goal and see personal progress
toward reaching that goal. Learners' goals should therefore connect to and
guide instruction.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider-wave-1%20%282%29.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
